President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Ambassador Ryan C. Crocker for the position of Member of the Broadcasting Board of Governors. Ambassador Crocker is currently the Kissinger Senior Fellow at Yale University and the James Schlesinger Distinguished Visiting Professor at the University of Virginia. He previously served as Ambassador to the Islamic Republic of Afghanistan and has had a distinguished 37-year career in the Foreign Service, including serving as U.S. Ambassador to Iraq, Pakistan, Syria, Kuwait, and Lebanon. Ambassador Crocker has received numerous awards for his service, including the Presidential Medal of Freedom and the Secretary of State's Distinguished Service Award. He holds a B.A. from Whitman College.